{"questionId":"22581838","questionHtml":"<p>Show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p>attempt to rearrange this equation to equal zero&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>recognizing their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>C</mi></msub></mrow></mfenced></math> is a factor of this expression&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR equivalent&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>, <em><strong>M1A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>\n<p>If a candidate divides by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> without justification, do not award the first <em><strong>A1</strong></em>, but all subsequent marks can still be awarded.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>use of quadratic formula to find roots,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></math>&nbsp;(and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>D</mi></msub></math>), of the quadratic&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR equivalent&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Condone a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>±</mo></math> in place of the minus sign, provided given answer is restated.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)(M0)A0M0A0M0A0</strong></em> for attempting to verify the given answer satisfies</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>x</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>n</mi><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p>attempt to rearrange this equation to equal zero&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>8</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>8</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>Recognise that their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>C</mi></msub></math> is a root of this equation&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>Attempt to find sum and product of roots&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>D</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;AND&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>×</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>D</mi></msub><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>×</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></mrow></mfenced><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mn>8</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>-</mo><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>use of quadratic formula to find roots, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>A</mi></msub></math> (and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>D</mi></msub></math>), of the quadratic&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mo>-</mo><msqrt><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mfrac><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mstyle><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR equivalent&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Condone a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>±</mo></math> in place of the minus sign, provided given answer is restated.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>x</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>m</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><msqrt><mn>5</mn></msqrt></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[7 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22581838","referenceCode":"24M.3.AHL.TZ1.2h","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that xA=m4-m45.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"h","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 7]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.12—Factor and remainder theorems, sum and product of roots"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}